      <hedline>
        <hl1>Sales Help at Your Elbow</hl1>
      </hedline>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>It is one thing for a customer to initiate contact with an online customer service representative by hitting a Help button. It is quite another level of invasion to have someone peering over one's shoulder -- or screen -- watching and recording every move. Worse is the ability to take control of one's computer from afar. Thanks for listing companies who employ this latest technology. I will avoid them in future.</p>
        <p>TOM SYKES  Appleton, Wis.</p>
      </block>
